{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2be995a-f380-45b2-bcb6-3a10d189da3d","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYour project just needs `EnableMSTestRunner` (which you already have). Here's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VrxbnAxjLSmWJW25rdosdv","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ddfa7a966b644827bab3bfc89e531632/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ddfa7a966b644827bab3bfc89e531632/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"cab0e6a1-c06b-4285-89c7-c4c20454a94e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about MTP support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt into MTP support, but in .NET 10 it's the default behavior and no longer required.\n\nLet me update their project file.","outputTokens":372,"requestId":"4C22:272C4C:D400C8:10880B9:6A012A3F"},"id":"1eb9316e-1bfa-47d2-aa9d-6c0a8a087dbc","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:00:54.437Z","parentId":"41090f98-18e1-4a9a-8506-3bb04062ef82"}
